Percutaneous puncture of the pancreas controlled by computerized tomography. The method of puncture biopsy under the control of computer tomography was used in 29 patients with diseases of the pancrease. Correct diagnosis was obtained in 27 patients. In 13 patients aimed biopsy was associated with the aspiration of cysts (in 7 patients) and drainage (in 6 patients). No complications of punctures of the pancreas under the control of computer tomography were noted.